nm-connection-editor

wired connection -> IP4 Settings, set method to "Shared to other computers" -> Save

Follow this instruction:
https://askubuntu.com/questions/359856/share-wireless-internet-connection-through-ethernet

type in ifconfig to find the new ip address and netmask number

go to the jetson board

set method: manual 
address: 10.42.0.69
Netmask: the one that you saw earlier
Gateway: the ip address that I saw
DNS servers: the ip address that I saw


Also, select the "Automatically connect to this network when it is available" in the General tab.
